In the 8th episode of Horizons of Leadership, we sit down with Lance Nelson, co-founder of Ordermoon, a bitcoin startup building a new payment infrastructure for restaurants using the Lightning Network for instant, low-cost transactions.

Lance left the UK to build his business in Eastern Europe, moving through multiple industries before identifying a fundamental problem in hospitality: outdated payment systems, high fees, and limited financial flexibility for restaurants. Today, Ordermoon is helping merchants accept Bitcoin seamlessly, build circular economies through its SatsBack model, and rethink how money should move in a digital world.

In this conversation, Lance shares his personal journey of moving from the UK to the Balkans, building his first businesses, and the lessons learned along the way. He explains how discovering Bitcoin changed his perspective on money, how that shift influenced the direction of Ordermoon. We also discuss the realities of building a startup, ethical decision-making, long-term thinking, AI, Blockchain and what founders often underestimate when creating something meaningful.

